🔧 Step-by-Step FIX (Do exactly)


---

🟢 Step 1: Extract Quay (bastion) CA cert

Run on bastion:

openssl s_client -connect bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443 -showcerts


---

👉 You will see output like:

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
MIIF...
-----END CERTIFICATE-----

👉 There may be multiple certs.

✔️ What to copy?

👉 Copy:

Root CA (best)
OR

Full chain (all certs) ✅ safest



---

🔧 Save it

vi quay-ca.crt

Paste:

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
...
-----END CERTIFICATE-----


---

🟢 Step 2: Combine with existing CA

👉 You already have Harbor CA in cluster

Now create combined file:

vi combined-ca.crt


---

Paste like this:

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
(Harbor CA)
-----END CERTIFICATE-----

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
(Quay CA)
-----END CERTIFICATE-----


---

⚠️ Rules:

No extra spaces

No \r\n

Proper new lines



---

🟢 Step 3: Update ConfigMap (BEST METHOD)

Run from cluster node:

oc create configmap harbor-ca \
  -n openshift-config \
  --from-file=ca-bundle.crt=combined-ca.crt \
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | oc apply -f -


---

👉 This safely replaces configmap


---

🟢 Step 4: Wait for rollout

watch oc get mcp

Wait until:

UPDATED=True
UPDATING=False
DEGRADED=False


---

🟢 Step 5: Validate from node (VERY IMPORTANT)

oc debug node/<node>
chroot /host

Then:

curl -vk https://bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443


---

✔️ Expected

No certificate error

Connection successful



---

🟢 Step 6: Validate release image

oc adm release info bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23


---

✔️ Must work

If this works → you are READY 🚀


---

🚀 Step 7: Upgrade

oc adm upgrade \
--to-image=bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23 \
--allow-explicit-upgrade


